Financial terms were not disclosed. According to Brazilian media Valor Economico, Cone SA will hold a minority stake in the project. Nevertheless, part of the Cone's portfolio of assets under management, located in Bahia state, are not subject of the current agreement. This is the second acquisition of warehouses that Blackstone is making in the country. On 25 November 2015 the company completed the purchase of 10 real estate properties from Brazilian real estate investment firm BR Properties for BRL 1.07bn (USD 310.4mn). Cone Suape's project portfolio comprises 13 warehouses with a total area of 331,000 m2 and hosts around 70 customers. Blackstone, established in 1985, is a global alternative investment firm with USD 310.5bn in assets under management as of 31 March 2015, allocated in real estate private equity funds, hedge funds, and mutual funds. With a team of over 1,600 employees and 23 offices in North America, Europe and the Asia-Pacific region, the company provides financial and strategic advisory services, restructuring and reorganisation advisory and fund placement services. Blackstone is listed on the New York Stock Exchange and booked a net profit of USD 1.58bn in 2014. ________________________________________________________________________________________ O grupo norte-americano de capital privado em participações Blackstone entrou em um acordo para adquirir uma participação majoritária no projeto Cone Suape de galpões (município de Cabo de Santo Agostinho, PE), operado pela gestora portuária e industrial Cone SA, fontes da mídia brasileira apuraram. Os termos financeiros não foram divulgados. Segundo a mídia brasileira Valor Econômico, a Cone SA vai deter uma participação minoritária no projeto. No entanto, parte da carteira de ativos sob gestão da Cone, localizados no Estado da Bahia, ficou de fora do negócio. Esta é a segunda aquisição de galpões que a Blackstone faz no Brasil. Em 25 de novembro de 2015, a empresa completou a compra de 10 imóveis da empresa brasileira de investimento imobiliário BR Properties, por BRL 1.07bn (USD 310.4mn). A carteira do projeto da Cone Suape está composta por 13 galpões com uma área total de 331,000 m2 que aluga para cerca de 70 clientes. A Blackstone, criada em 1985, é uma empresa global de investimentos alternativos com USD 310.5bn em ativos sob gestão, até à data de 31 de março de 2015, alocados em fundos de investimento imobiliário de capital privado, fundos hedge e fundos mútuos. UnitedHealth and Samariano have not confirmed the information, yet. According to the Brazilian online journal Folha, Hospital Samaritano used to be administrated by a charity entity that had to sell the business in order to receive financial resources that will invest in other philanthropic initiatives. Upon the completion of the deal, the hospital will start operating as a for-profit company, losing its philanthropy certificate and having to pass through certain procedures. Hospital Samaritano, established in 1894 and based in Sao Paulo city (Sao Paulo state, Brazil), operates as a clinical and surgical services provider, specialised in cardiology, gastroenterology, neurology, orthopedics, oncology, urology, and others areas. The company has more than 2,300 employees and registered a turnover of BRL 437.9mn (USD 116.3mn) in 2014. Since February 2011 the firm is a 83.94% owned subsidiary of local healthcare services provider Empresa de Servicos Hospitalares Ltda (ESHO). On 26 November 2015, Hospital Samaritano was recognised as the second best hospital in Brazil and the sixth best hospital in Latin America. UHG, established in 1974, is a diversified health and well-being group with operations in two business platforms: UnitedHealthcare (health care coverage and benefits services), and Optum (information and technology-enabled health services), serving customers in 50 states in the U.S. and in 125 other countries worldwide. UHG is listed on the New York Stock Exchange, has around 185,000 employees, and reached a turnover of USD 130.5bn and a net income of USD 5.62bn in 2014. __________________________________________________________________________________________________________ A empresa de saúde norte-americana UnitedHealth Group Inc (UHG) entrou em um acordo para a aquisição da operadora brasileira de hospital Sociedade Hospital Samaritano Ltda, por BRL 1.3bn (USD 345.4mn), fontes da mídia brasileira apuraram. Após � conclusão do negócio, o hospital passa a operar como uma empresa com fins lucrativos, perdendo o seu certificado de filantropia, e vai ter que passar por certos procedimentos. A Hospital Samaritano, fundada em 1894 e sediada na cidade de São Paulo (SP, Brasil), atua como um provedora de serviços clínicos e cirúrgicos, especializada em cardiologia, gastroenterologia, neurologia, ortopedia, oncologia, urologia, e em outras áreas. A empresa emprega mais de 2,300 colaboradores e registrou um faturamento de BRL 437.9mn (USD 116.3mn) em 2014. Desde Fevereiro de 2011 a empresa opera como uma subsidiária detida a 83.94% da local provedora de serviços de saúde Empresa de Servicos Hospitalares Ltda (ESHO). 113883 27/11/2015 巴西 Mallinckrodt do Brasil Ltda 收购 Guerbet LLC 法国 Mallinckrodt PLC 医药制造 (3254) 　 　 100 French medical equipment manufacturer Guerbet LLC has purchased Mallinckrodt do Brasil Ltda, the Brazilian subsidiary of U.S. specialty pharmaceutical product manufacturer Mallinckrodt PLC for an undisclosed sum. The information was provided to DealWatch by Demarest Advogados that acted as legal advisor to Guerbet LLC. The transaction is part of a global deal that includes Mallinckrodt's contrast media and delivery system business in Australia, Brazil, Chile, Colombia, France, Ireland, China, Italy, Luxembourg, Netherlands, Panama, Poland, South Africa, South Korea, Spain, Sweden, Switzerland, Turkey, U.K. and U.S., and has a total value of approximately USD 270mn. Guerbet acted through its Brazilian subsidiaries Guerbet SA and Guerbet Produtos Radiologicos Ltda. Demarest said that the acquisition of Mallinckrodt's contrast media and delivery systems business is an excellent opportunity for Guerbet to reinforce its X-ray business and develops its Imaging Solutions and Services business. In addition, it will accelerate Guerbet's international expansion and will provide it with commercial and industrial complementarities, in order to rationalise certain operating costs. Guerbet LLC operates as a research pharmaceutical company and contrast media manufacturer for radiology and magnetic resonance imaging. The company had a revenue of EUR 409mn (USD 543.6mn) and a net income of EUR 26mn (USD 34.6mn) in 2014. Mallinckrodt PLC manufactures and sells specialty pharmaceutical products and diagnostic imaging, including generic drugs and imaging agents. The company manufactures pain management medications and offers its products to major wholesalers and retail drug store chains worldwide. Mallinckrodt had a turnover of USD 3.5bn and a net income of USD 325mn for fiscal year ended 30 September 2015. ________________________________________________________________________________ A fabricante francesa de equipamentos médicos Guerbet LLC adquiriu a Mallinckrodt do Brasil Ltda, a filial brasileira da fabricante norte-americana de produtos farmacêuticos especiais Mallinckrodt PLC, por um valor não revelado. A informação foi fornecida para o DealWatch pelo Demarest Advogados que atuou como assessor jurídico da Guerbet LLC. A operação faz parte de um acordo global que inclui os negócios de agentes de contraste e sistema de distribuição da Mallinckrodt na Austrália, Brasil, Chile, Colômbia, França, Irlanda, China, Itália, Luxemburgo, os Países Baixos, Panamá, Polônia, África do Sul, Coreia do Sul, Espanha, Suécia, Suíça, Turquia, o Reino Unido e os EUA, e tem um valor total de aproximadamente USD 270mn. A Guerbet agiu por meio das suas subsidiárias brasileiras Guerbet SA e Guerbet Produtos Radiológicos Ltda. O Demarest disse que a aquisição do negócio de agentes de contraste e sistemas de distribuição da Mallinckrodt é uma excelente oportunidade para a Guerbet reforçar o seu segmento de raios-X e desenvolver as suas soluções e serviços de imagem. Além disso, a operação vai acelerar a expansão internacional da Guerbet e vai fornecr serviços comerciais e industriais complementares, a fim de racionalizar certos custos de exploração. A Guerbet LLC opera como uma empresa de pesquisa farmacéutica e como fabricante de meios de contraste, utilizados na radiologia e imagiologia por ressonância magnética. A empresa teve um faturamento de EUR 409mn (USD 543.6mn) e um lucro líquido de EUR 26mn (USD 34.6mn) em 2014. A Mallinckrodt PLC fabrica e comercializa produtos farmacêuticos especiais e diagnóstico por imagem, incluindo medicamentos genéricos e agentes de imagem. A empresa fabrica medicamentos contra dor e oferece os seus produtos para grandes atacadistas e redes de lojas varejistas de medicamentos no mundo inteiro. A Mallinckrodt teve um faturamento de USD 3.5bne um lucro líquido de USD 325mn para o ano fiscal findo em 30 de setembro de 2015.

Financial details were not disclosed. As part of the agreement, CPR Impex committed to settle the outstanding debts of SFS in the total amount of EUR 22.0mn (USD 23.35mn). Furthermore, the buyer plans to take over the remaining 44% stake from the Bulgarian company. So far, CPR Impex has settled part of SFS's debts amounting to RSD 600mn (USD 5.25mn / EUR 5.0mn). The move was necessary to unblock the target's bank accounts. The deal will enable troubled SFS to avoid bankruptcy proceedings. At the moment, SFS is facing problems due to expensive raw materials and abnormal high prices of gas and electricity, but it expects that the Serbian government will bring down these expenses to normal levels. SFS, established in 1907, produces container glass, table ware glass, technical and optical glass, and it employs around 850 people. The company was taken over in 2012 by international group Glass Industry, affiliated with Bulgarian businessman Tsvetan Vasilev, who is currently having legal troubles with Serbian authorities and is awaiting extradition.

113568 27/11/2015 斯洛文尼亚 Paloma dd 私有化 Abris Capital Partners 波兰 Slovenian State Holding (SDH) 造纸业 (322) 15.92 (官方数据) 　 UPDATE: On 01 June 2016, Polish investment fund Abris Capital has cancelled its bid to take over Slovenian state-owned hygienic tissue producer Paloma, Paloma announced in a press release. ORIGINAL: The national investment fund Slovenian State Holding (SDH) said it has agreed with the capital increase in local hygiene and tissue paper producer Paloma d.d. by Polish PE fund Abris Capital Partners in the amount of EUR 15.0mn (USD 15.9mn). The recapitalisation deal in which Abris is offering EUR 3.30 per share, is part of a privatisation plan of Paloma. The stake being acquired in Paloma was not disclosed. The public tender for the share capital increase in Paloma was issued in February 2015, and it will be considered successful if the potential investor acquires at least one-third of the voting rights in the company. Completion of the transaction is still subject to fulfillment of certain conditions precedent, including regulatory approval. Once the current transaction is completed, Abris will be obliged to publish a takeover bid for the remaining shares. Thus, the existing shareholders, including SDH (which currently holds a 70.97% stake in the company), will have the option to sell their Paloma shares to Abris at the same offer price of EUR 3.30 apiece. The raised proceeds will go towards the modernisation and development of Paloma production capacities, and for improving its efficiency and financial results. Founded in 1885, Paloma d.d. was placed in 2013 on a list of 15 state firms earmarked for privatization. The company is based in Sladki Vrh, near the border with Austria in north-eastern Slovenia, and manufactures toilet paper, kitchen rolls, napkins, tissues, universal towels, industrial towels, medical towels, folded toilet paper and maxi-roll toilet paper. With around 700 employees, Paloma is present in more than 30 markets, and has an annual paper production capacity of some 72,000 tons. For 2014, it booked revenues of EUR 87.0mn. Mr. Adam Tan, President of HNA Group, said that the acquisition is expected to bring a greater choice and convenience to the HNA's customers traveling to and from Brazil. According to Mr. David Neeleman, CEO of Azul, HNA has decided to invest in the company, due to its strong potential for future growth and winning business model. The transaction will give time to Azul to plan better an eventual initial public offering (IPO), local media reported. Azul, headquartered in the municipality of Barueri (Sao Paulo state, Brazil), is the largest Brazilian airline in terms of network-size. The company provides passenger and cargo air transportation services in Brazil with 145 aircrafts that serves more than 900 daily flights to more than 100 destinations. Azul is a wholly owned subsidiary of local passenger airline operator Azul SA. Azul had a turnover of 4.7bn (USD 2bn) and a net profit of BRL 80.57mn (USD 34.34mn) in 2014. HNA, founded in 1993, is mainly focused on providing airlines services. The company also operates in the real estate, hotel and catering, logistics and transportation, financial and network information technology services through its affiliated businesses HNA Aviation, HNA Holdings, HNA Capital, HNA Tourism and HNA Logistics. The Chinese company has 110,000 employees and recorded revenues of USD 25.6bn in 2014. _______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________ A empresa aérea brasileira Azul Linhas Aéreas Brasileiras SA anunciou que o conglomerado chinês HNA Group Co Ltd adquirir 23.7% do seu capital social, por BRL 1.7bn (USD 456.7mn). Mr. Kaz Matsuyama, President and CEO of Sato Holdings, said that the acquisition not only strengthens the company's primary label business presence in Latin America, but also its labels operations across the entire Sato Group. He added that the transaction aligns with the Sato's core mid-term objectives for the period 2015 - 2017 for globalisation of the business through expansion to emerging markets. Prakolar, established in 1967 in Sao Paulo city (Sao Paulo state, Brazil), produces self-adhesives for pharmaceutical, cosmetic, foodstuff, chemical, beverage, and other industries. The company operates an industrial complex of over 5,000 m2 and serves global, regional and local brands. Sato is a global developer and producer of labelling systems, automatic identification and data collection solutions. The Company also operates in businesses related to shared services, print contract services, cargo delivery, electronic equipment inspection, assembly, and others. Sato is listed on the Tokyo Stock Exchange and reported a turnover of JPY 99.8bn (USD 918.45mn) and a net income of JPY 3.79bn (USD 34.87mn) in the fiscal year ended 31 March 2015. _______________________________________________________________________________________________________________ A fabricante japonesa de soluções eletrônicas Sato Holdings Corp anunciou que adquiriu a totalidade do capital social da fabricante brasileira de rótulos autoadesivos para decoração Prakolar Rotulos Auto Adesivos SA, por um valor não revelado. Ele acrescentou que a transação estava em linha com os principais objetivos da Sato de médio prazo, para o período 2015 - 2017, para conseguir globalização dos seus negócios através de expansão para mercados emergentes. A Prakolar, criada em 1967 na cidade de São Paulo (SP, Brasil), produz autoadesivos para as indústrias farmacêutica, cosmética, alimentícia, química e de bebidas, entre outras. A empresa opera um complexo industrial de mais de 5,000 m2 e serve marcas globais, regionais e locais. 113349 20/11/2015 俄罗斯 RussNeft 少数股权购买 Glencore Plc 瑞士 　 石油和天然气的开采 (211) 1,500.00 (官方数据) 46 Swiss commodities trader Glencore has acquired a 46% stake in Russian oil and gas firm Russneft as a result of a debt-to-equity conversion in October 2015, according to reports of RBC news agency and Vedomosti daily. RBC cited an official representative of Russneft as saying that Glencore wrote off USD 1.5bn of Russneft's debt against shares in the company. The same amount was also written off by structures of Mikhail Gutseriev, the hitherto sole owner of Russneft. Following the conversion, Gutseriev reduced his holdings in the target to 54% while the company's overall debt fell to USD 2.3bn from USD 5.3bn. The conversion plans were reported by Glencore back in March 2015 when the latter intended to buy a 49% stake in Russneft. In May 2015, the deal configuration changed and this percentage fell to 46%. Thus the transaction did not need approval by the Government Commission on Foreign Investments. Russneft reportedly plans to further shorten its obligations by USD 1bn until the end of 2015 and expects an EBITDA of USD 470mn in 2015. Gutseriev earlier voiced plans to unite Russneft with his company Neftisa until the end of 2016 and then conduct and IPO, valuing the united company at USD 18bn. RussNeft claims to be one of Russia`s top ten oil and gas companies. The group has 45 production subsidiaries and operates in 16 regions of Russia and CIS. In 2014, its annual oil output was 8.6 million tonnes. The company's recoverable reserves of oil and gas are measured at 765 million tonnes and 177bn m3 respectively. In 2014, RussNeft generated RUB 102.4bn (USD 2.71bn) in sales. Glencore is a leading integrated producer and marketer of commodities, with worldwide activities in the marketing of metals and minerals, energy products and agricultural products and the production, refinement, processing, storage and transport of these products. The group has assets in over 50 countries. In 2014, Glencore Plc posted USD 221.1bn in revenue. Note: The amount of debt converted by Glencore in exchange for its 46% stake is taken as deal value.
113348 20/11/2015 俄罗斯 Business News Media 收购 Demyan Kudryavtsev - private investor 俄罗斯 Dow Jones & Co; Pearson Plc 报纸、期刊、图书和字典的出版 (5111) 7.13 (市场估计) 66.6 U.S. financial publisher Dow Jones & Co and U.K.-based publishing and education company Pearson Plc agreed to divest their 33.3% stakes in Russian company Business News Media, the publisher of Vedomosti business daily, to Demyan Kydryavtsev, a local entrepreneur and former general director of Russian publishing house Kommersant, according to a joint press statement of the sellers and a report of Vedomosti daily. The amount of the transaction will remain confidential as mutually agreed by the deal parties. A source close to the transaction details told Vedomosti that the newspaper was valued at more than EUR 10mn (USD 10.7mn), including debt. According to unofficial information of RBC news agency, the larger part of the payment will be in form of acquiring the debt obligations of Business News Media towards Pearson and Dow Jones. In the frames of the deal, the obligations will be reportedly acquired by Martin Pompadur, a board member of Business News Media and former top manager of Dow Jones’ parent - News Corp. The transaction is due to close by the end of 2015. The sale comes as a result of the latest Russian legislative regulations, according to which foreign entities are prohibited from having more than 20% interest in Russian media companies starting from 2016. After the deal completion, Kudryavtsev will consolidate 100% in Vedomosti, having already bought the first 33.3% interest in the daily in April 2015 from Finnish media group Sanoma Corp. The current divestment marks the exit of two of the last major foreign investors on the Russian media market, following several similar transactions earlier in the year. The sales contract prevents Kudryavtsev from re-selling the newspaper to a third party for a certain period of time, according to unofficial information of The Financial Times. In an interview with Russian Forbes Kydravtsev voiced intention to possibly sell his media assets in the future. Vedomosti has been published since 1999. Its circulation is 75,000 copies. The daily claims for accuracy, competence, speed and impartiality.

The deal is subject to certain closing conditions, including the approval by Singapore's principal industrial estates developer and manager JTC Corp. The property is used as a warehouse primarily for the storage of Teho International's fibre ropes. Following the proposed disposal, Teho International plans to consolidate its warehousing facilities in one location by optimizing the space utilization of its remaining warehouse. Teco Electric & Machinery Co Ltd produces high efficiency motors, inverter duty motors and explosion proof motors. It also manufactures, installs and retails electrical and mechanical equimpent. The company is listed on the Taiwan Stock Exchange and it booked revenues of TWD 53.8bn (USD 1.7bn) for 2014. Teho International Inc Ltd supplies rigging and mooring equipment to the marine and offshore oil & gas industries. Its products include steel wire rope, synthetic fibre sling, electric heating and associated control systems, marine and offshore oil and gas fire dampers louvers and galley hoods. The company's shares are listed on the Singapore Exchange and its revenue were SGD 61.65mn (USD 44.76mn) for FY ended 30 June 2015. In May 2014, Teho International has acquired local real estate developer TIEC Holdings Pte Ltd for USD 12.3mn (USD 9.7mn); in a move to diversify into property development and investment business, with focus on Singapore, Malaysia, Thailand, the Philippines, Japan, Australia and the UK.

UPDATE 1: On 03 December 2015, the Hungarian Competition Office (GVH) has approved the acquisition of a majority stake in the Budapest Stock Exchange (BSE) by the National Bank of Hungary (MNB), the state news agency MTI reported. ORIGINAL: Hungary's central bank Magyar Nemzeti Bank (MNB) announced it has agreed to acquire a majority stake in the local Budapest Stock Exchange (BSE) for a total deal value of HUF 13.22bn (USD 45.57mn). MNB will acquire a 50.46% stake in BSE from Austrian CEE Stock Exchange Group (CEESEG) and another 18.34% stake in the target from Austrian special-purpose bank Österreichische Kontrollbank (ÖKB AG). CEESEG will sell 2.731 million shares of the bourse operator, while ÖKB AG will divest 993,100 BSE shares for HUF 3,550 (USD 12.13) apiece. Following the deal, MNB which currently owns a 6.94% stake in the local bourse, will increase its ownership to 75.74%. Once the transaction is completed, MNB will also launch a takeover bid to the remaining shareholders. The deal is in line with the buyer's commitment to become a majority holder of the bourse in order to help support the pro-growth policies of the government. Budapest Stock Exchange (Budapesti Ertektozsde Zrt. or BÉT), founded in 1864, is a major market in Central Eastern Europe by market capitalization and liquidity. As of 30 June 2015, it registered 46 listed companies and a Market Cap. of EUR 15.2bn. One of the BSE's major assets is its 46.7% stake in central equity clearing house Keler, whose net capital could reach HUF 29.0bn by end-2015. The CEE Stock Exchange Group, founded in 2010, is a holding company comprising the stock exchanges of Vienna, Budapest, Ljubljana and Prague. In 2014, it had a market capitalization of EUR 135bn. Recently, in July 2015, CEESEG announced the sale of Slovenian stock exchange Ljubljanska borza (LJSE) to Croatian counterpart Zagrebačka burza (ZSE) for an undisclosed amount.

The transaction is subject to completion of closing conditions. The winning bid was placed by investment vehicle Viva Edge, led by Bulgarian private investor Spas Roussev and in which VTB Capital and U.S. investment group Tennenbaum Capital also participate, according to Bulgarian weekly Capital. The other bidder in the auction was Greek businessman Panos Germanos backed by U.S. investment firm Third Point of distressed debt investor Daniel Loeb. The total cash and debt-free consideration for the acquisition is around EUR 700mn (USD 750mn), according to Capital. VTB Capital was forced to call the auction after InterV defaulted on a EUR 150mn (USD 160.5mn) bridge financing loan borrowed to acquire 94% of BTC in 2012. InterV, which is controlled by Bulgarian banker Tsvetan Vasilev, VTB and BTC senior debt holders, led by Tennenbaum, later raised its stake in the telecom to almost 100%. Tsvetan Vasilev's bank Corporate Commercial Bank (CCB) went bankrupt in late 2014 and most of his assets are blocked by the authorities. Corporate Commercial Bank was Bulgaria's fourth largest lender at the time when its license was revoked by the country's central bank. BTC, trading as Vivacom, is a former state monopoly and Bulgaria's dominant fixed-line operator. It owns the country's third largest mobile operator Vivatel. The company posted net sales of BGN 805.9mn (USD 412.1mn/USD 546.6mn) and a net profit of BGN 26.3mn (EUR 13.5mn/USD 17.8mn) for 2014. Spas Roussev is the former owner of telecoms network company Telelink. In recent years he acquired Interhotel Grand-Hotel Sofia and Hilton Sofia.

Heraeus Vectra is an innovative international high-tech company that manufactures precious metal compounds. The company uses the mechanism of dispersion hardening (DPH) which is a heat treatment technique used to increase the yield strength of malleable materials. By using this technique, the company creates a new class of materials in precious metal technology whose resistance to thermal loadings and corrosion is even greater than that of pure platinum and the solid solution hardened platinum alloys. PGM Technologies Inc is a service based business that develops and implements processes and recovery techniques to maximise the yield from precious metals recovery exercise. The company has destructive treatment facilities in Sweetwater and at the Heraeus refinery in Wartburg city (Tennessee state, U.S.) Heraeus Holding, created in 1851, specialises in the manufacturing and sale of precious metals, materials and technologies, sensors, biomaterials, medical and dental products, quartz glass and specialty light sources. A Heraeus Vectra é uma empresa internacional inovadora de alta tecnologia que fabrica componentes de metais preciosos. A empresa utiliza o mecanismo de endurecimento por dispersão (DPH), que é uma técnica de tratamento térmico utilizada para aumentar a resistência ao escoamento de materiais maleáveis. Usando esta técnica, a empresa conseguiu criar uma nova classe de materiais em tecnologia de metal precioso, cuja resistência a cargas térmicas e de resistência � corrosão é ainda maior do que a da platina pura e os sólidos da solução ligas de platina endurecidos. Shanda Group started out as an online game company called Shanda Interactive in 1999. Amber operates in 14 countries and employs over 45,000 people. Ambev booked BRL 38.08bn (USD 16.2bn) in revenues and a net profit of BRL 12.07bn (USD 5.14bn) in 2014. The company is listed on the BM&FBovespa and the New York (NYSE) Stock Exchanges. Mark Anthony Group, founded in 1972, is an alcohol beverages manufacturer. The company produces and distributes fine wine, spirits and premium beers. It has three product lines: beers, spirits and specialty beverages, that are produced in several countries across North America and Europe, and in South Africa. The sale is part of Orange SA's strategy to optimize its assets portfolio in one of its priority regions - Africa and Middle-East. The remaining 30% stake in the operator remains in the hands of the National Treasury. Founded in 1999, Telkom Kenya is a former monopoly in the fixed-line telecom services in the country. Apart from that, the company provides internet as well as 3G, CDMA, GSM and Wimax wireless telecommunications solutions, being the third largest player on the mobile market. As at end-June 2015, Telkom Kenya had 4 million mobile subscribers. In 2014, Telkom Kenya posted KES 9.2bn (USD 103mn) in sales, up by 5% y/y. U.K.-based Helios Investment Partners operates a family of funds and their related co-investment entities, aggregating more than USD 3bn in capital commitments. The company pursues a full range of investment types, including business formations, growth equity investments, structured investments in listed entities and large-scale leveraged acquisitions across Africa.

112913 09/11/2015 澳大利亚 Santos Ltd 少数股权购买 Hony Capital Group LP 中国 Santos Ltd 石油和天然气的开采 (211); 管道运输 (486) 351.94 (官方数据) 4.16 Australian oil and gas company Santos Ltd has raised AUD 500mn (USD 351.9mn) from Chinese investment firm Hony Capital, the former disclosed. Hony Capital, through its United Faith Ventures Ltd, subscribed to 73,529,412 ordinary shares of Santos at AUSD 6.8 (USD 4.8) apiece. The price represents a 15% premium to the company's closing price of AUD 5.91(USD 4.2) on 06 November 2015. The transaction is part of the AUD 3.5bn (USD 2.5bn) strategic recapitalisation plan of Santos to reduce its debt. Under the plan, Santos will sell its 35% non-operated interest in the Kipper gas field to Mitsui E&P Australia Pty Ltd for AUD 520mn (USD 366mn). Santos will also raise AUD 2.5bn (USD 1.8bn) through a fully underwritten accelerated pro-rata renounceable entitlement offer. Upon the completion of the transaction, Hony and its affiliates will own 7.9% of Santos' issued capital up from the current 1.4%. In addition, Hony has agreed to not increase its holdings in Santos above 9.9% for three months. Santos Ltd develops, produces, markets, supplies and transports oil and gas products in Australia and some Asian countries. The company's products include gas, ethane, liquefied gas, LPG and other related products. Santos Ltd is listed on the Australian Stock Exchange and booked revenues of AUD 4bn (USD 3.3bn) for FY ended 31 December 2014. Hony Capital is a Chinese private equity firm investing in the construction materials, pharmaceuticals, construction machinery, consumer goods, and retail industries. It is sponsored by Legend Holdings, parent of Hong Kong-listed multinational technology firm Lenovo Group. Note: The deal stake was calculated using the target's outstanding shares of approximately 1.8 billion after the private placement and entitlement offer.

The sum is equal to approximately 50% of past costs incurred by Africa Oil prior to the agreed 31 March 2015 effective date. Also, Maersk will reimburse Africa Oil for its acquired working interest share of costs incurred between the effective date and the closing date of the transaction. 112666 02/11/2015 巴西 Beauty and Personal Care Business of Hypermarcas SA 收购 Coty Inc 美国 Hypermarcas SA 日用化学产品制造 (3256) 984.1 (官方数据) 100 UPDATE 2: On 28 December 2015, Hypermarcas announced the completion of the transaction. Coty has already paid BRL 1.71bn (USD 433.6mn) and the remaining amount of BRL 2.09bn (USD 530mn) will be paid after the fulfillment of certain conditions. UPDATE 1: On 4 December 2015, the transaction received the approval of the Brazilian Antitrust Authority CADE. ORIGINAL: U.S. fragrance and beauty products company Coty Inc announced it has entered into a definitive agreement to acquire Beauty and Personal Care Business of Brazilian personal care and hygiene products manufacturer Hypermarcas SA for BRL 3.8bn (USD 984.1mn). The deal value will be paid in a combination of cash on hand and debt facilities. Hypermarcas will use the proceeds to reduce its net debt, Brazilian media sources reported. Under the agreement, Coty will acquire Hypermarcas' brands such as: Monange, offering female body moisturizers, deodorants and hair products; Risque, a nail polishes, hands, feet, and hypoallergenic treatment line; Bozzano, a brand in the male care segment; Paixao, a skin care brand; and Biocolor, offering hair colorants for men and women. The transaction does not include Hypermarcas' child care products, preservatives, sweeteners and skin cosmetics divisions. Hypermarcas commented that its plan is to focus on the pharmaceutical market and the partnership with Coty will be beneficial for achieving this goal. According to Mr. Bart Becht, Interim CEO and Chairman of COTY, the acquisitions will provide Coty with a critical mass retail platform for Procter & Gamble's products to the third largest beauty market in the world. He added that Coty expects to enhance its competitive position towards becoming a global leader in the world's beauty industry, by adding Hypermarcas' strong brand and highly qualified leadership team. Mr. Bart Becht also said that Coty will shift to areas such as make-up and celebrity perfumes, in order to attract younger customers. The transaction is subject to regulatory approvals and the fulfilment of certain conditions. It is expected to be completed in the second half of 2016. Hypermarcas, founded in 2001, is a consumer goods company, engaged in the development, production, and sale of generics, prescription and OTC medicines, beauty and personal care products under the brand names Monange, Bozzano, NeoQuimica, Risque, Jontex, Sanifill, Neosoro, Gelol, and Episol. Hypermarcas is listed on the BM&FBovespa Stock Exchange and reached a turnover of BRL 4.68bn (USD 1.74bn) and a net income of BRL 402.7mn (USD 171.63mn) in 2014. Coty, founded in 1904, specializes in manufacturing and distribution of fragrances, cosmetics, skin and body care products under the brands of Adidas, Calvin Klein, Chloe, Davidoff, Marc Jacobs, OPI, Philosophy, Playboy, Rimmel, and Sally Hansen in more than 130 countries. The company has production facilities in the United States, the United Kingdom, France, Spain and China, and engages more than 10,000 employees. Coty reached a turnover of USD 4.4bn and a net revenue of USD 233mn in the FY ending 30 June 2015. In July 2015, Coty agreed to pay P&G USD 12.5 billion for 43 brands to expand beyond perfumes. ______________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________________ UPDATE 2: Em 28 de dezembro de 2015, a Hypermarcas anunciou o fechamento da operação. A parcela de BRL 1.71bn (USD 433.6mn) já foi paga pela Coty e o valor remanescente de BRL 2.09bn (USD 530mn) vai ser pago depois da implementação de certas condições previstas no contrato de compra e venda. UPDATE 1: Em 4 de dezembro de 2015 a operação obteve o aval do Conselho Administrativo de Defesa Econômica (CADE). Pelo acordo, a Coty vai adquirir as seguintes marcas da Hypermarcas: a Monange, que oferece hidratantes corporais, desodorantes e produtos capilares femininos; a Risque, uma linha de esmaltes e produtos para cuidados de mãos e pés; a Bozzano, uma marca destinada para a higiene masculina; a Paixao, uma linha de cuidados da pele e a Biocolor que atua no mercado de coloração para os cabelos femininos e masculinos. Ele acrescentou que a Coty esperava fortalecer a sua posição competitiva para se tornar um líder global na indústria da beleza, através da incorporação da marca forte da Hypermarcas e o seu equipe executivo altamente qualificado. O Sr. Bart Becht disse também que a Coty ia focar-se na comercialização de maquiagem e perfumes de celebridades, a fim de atrair clientes mais jovens. A transação está sujeita a aprovações regulatórias e ao cumprimento de determinadas condições. O fechamento do negócio está previsto para o segundo semestre de 2016. A Hypermarcas, fundada em 2001, é uma empresa de bens de consumo, com atuação no desenvolvimento, produção e comercialização de medicamentos de venda livre, medicamentos isentos de prescrição médica, genéricos, produtos de beleza e higiene pessoal sob as marcas Monange, Bozzano, NeoQuímica, Risque, Jontex, Sanifill, Neosoro, Gelol e Episol. Listada na Bolsa de Valores de São Paulo BM&FBovespa, a Hypermarcas atingiu um volume de negócios de BRL 4.68bn (USD 1.74bn) e um lucro líquido de BRL 402.7mn (USD 149.86mn) em 2014. A Coty, fundada em 1904, é especializada na fabricação e distribuição de perfumes, cosméticos, produtos para o cuidado da pele e do corpo sob as marcas Adidas, Calvin Klein, Chloe, Davidoff, Marc Jacobs, OPI, Filosofia, Playboy, Rimmel e Sally Hansen em mais de 130 países. A empresa tem fábricas nos Estados Unidos, Reino Unido, França, Espanha e China, e envolve mais de 10,000 colaboradores. A Coty atingiu um volume de negócios de USD 4.4bn e um lucro líquido de USD 233mn no exercício findo em 30 de junho de 2015. A Cap Gemini prove os seus serviços a prestadores de serviços financeiros e para as indústrias petrolífera, automotiva, aeroespacial e de telecomunicações na Europa, Estados Unidos, Ásia e África do Sul. The value of the transaction was kept confidential by the two parties. The transaction was carried out through newly-established subsidiary MFB Real Estate (MFBI), wholly-owned by MFB Zrt. Following the deal, MFBI will continue to operate and utilize the building in compliance with existing functions and valid tenancy contracts. MFBI does not plan further acquisitions in the real estate market. Párisi Nagyáruház (Paris Grand Department Store) was built in 1882 as the country's first modern department store. The property was rebuilt in 2011 following a devastating fire. In 2005, Orco Property Group acquired the building and refurbished it with an investment of EUR 17.0mn. Its tenants include Alexandra retail book store, the internet firm Ustream, while the building's famous Lotz Hall is home to a cafe shop. Founded in 1991, Orco Property Group is an investor, developer and asset manager in the Central European real estate and hospitality market. The company focuses mainly on Germany, the Czech Republic, Hungary, Poland, Croatia and Slovakia. Its shares are listed on the Paris Stock Exchange and the Warsaw Stock Exchange. The transaction is part of Mitsui's BRL 19.5bn (USD 5bn) Euro Medium Term Note Programme. Upon the transaction being terminated, Mitsui expects to maintain and strengthen its strategic partnership and alliance with Dow. The deal is subject to regulatory approvals and is expected to close by 12 July 2016. SVAA, headquartered in the municipality of Santa Vitoria (Minas Gerais state, Brazil), produces and distributes bio-ethylene, bio-polyethylene and sugarcane derived chemicals. The company was founded in 2011 as a 50/50 joint venture between Mitsui and Dow Quimica SA, a subsidiary of Dow. It operates around 36,000 hectares of plantation and an industrial park, having a processing capacity of 2.7 million tons of sugarcane and a productive capacity of up to 240 million litres of ethanol per harvest. Dow Chemical, established in 1897, is an international manufacturer and supplier of chemical products. The company provides more than 5,000 products within four segments: specialty chemicals, advanced materials, agrosciences and plastics, and operates 188 manufacturing plants in 36 countries, engaging 52,700 employees. Dow Chemical is listed on the New York Stock Exchange, and posted USD 58bn in revenues and USD 69bn in net assets in 2014. Mitsui & Co Ltd, established in 1947, is a global diversified trading company with interests in the energy, machinery and infrastructure, metals, chemicals, food, textile, logistics, and finance sectors. The company operates a network of 150 offices in 67 countries worldwide, and engages more than 44,800 employees.
